    <p><strong>Can’t Miss Last Minute Deadlines and Tips for CES</strong><br> 
by Michelle Griffin</p>
    <p>
        <p>It’s already December, and the 2012 International CES is only one month away. We are so excited for the 2012 CES, and we cannot wait to see all of you in Vegas in January. Remember, this year’s show runs on a Tuesday through Friday schedule (unlike the past few years). Additionally, we have more exhibits at The Venetian, including the new Eureka Park and PMA@CES that will run alongside Venetian mainstays like high-performance audio exhibitors and the Innovations Design and Engineering Awards Showcase. <br />
        With the craze of the holidays and with normal tradeshow prep in full swing, it’s easy to let important tasks slip through the cracks. Be sure you don’t fall behind! Here are three handy tips to help you along the way.<br />
        <br />
        1) <strong>Review the Deadline Checklist</strong>. Managing deadlines can be difficult. However, we’ve made it easy for you. Check out the <a  target="_blank" href="http://www.cesweb.org/docs/LVCC_Hilton_Deadline_Checklist%286%29.pdf">Deadline Checklist</a> that our Operations team meticulously assembled for you. Here, you’ll find the work order due dates for all official CES vendors. Some important deadlines coming up include the GES discount deadlines on both December 12 and December 21. Security orders and Freeman AV forms are due December 12 as well. Refer to it often. This <a  target="_blank" href="http://www.cesweb.org/docs/LVCC_Hilton_Deadline_Checklist%286%29.pdf">checklist</a> will become your right-hand helper in the next month.<br />
        <br />
        2) <strong>Take Advantage of the CES Pre-Registered Media List.</strong> The pre-registered media list contains contact information for all of the media that have registered for the 2012 International CES. For your convenience, the list will be accessible via CESweb.org starting today (December 1). To download the list, enter your company name and exhibitor ID number, which you can find on your show invoice. Please contact your sales representative or send an email to <a  href="mailto:prcontacts@CE.org">prcontacts@CE.org</a> for assistance.<br />
        <br />
        3) <strong>Prepare and Distribute Your Paperless CES Press Kits.</strong> Both the LVCC and Venetian press rooms will house electronic exhibitor press kits for the 2012 International CES. This means you are welcome to put your paper-saving press kits in two areas (USB, disc or online format that you host and make known with a one-page spec sheet (8.5" x 11” max) that lists media contacts and the URL where your electronic press kit is located). Printed press materials greater than one page in length should be stored in the exhibitor’s booth. Make sure your press kit is marked clearly with the company’s name and CES booth number. Press kits are a one-stop source for the media to get information about your company and products. Information included in kits should be kept simple and to the point; remember, journalists are working fast and are after hard news.<br />
        <br />
        For more information concerning operations and logistics at CES, check the Operations <a  target="_blank" href="http://www.cesweb.org/exhibitors/showPlanning/default.asp">show planning pages</a> on CESweb.org. Also, for more PR tips be sure to refer to your <a  target="_blank" href="http://www.cesweb.org/docs/2012_Exhibitior_PR_Kit_08.30.11.pdf">Exhibitor PR Kit</a>.<br />
        <br />
        Sincerely,<br />
        <br />
        Michelle Griffin </p>
